        { "type": "text", "id": "rp2-1", "variant": "heading", "content": "Executive summary" },
        { "type": "text", "id": "rp2-2", "variant": "body", "content": "Attachments are where attention goes to die. Across the sessions we studied, the median PDF was abandoned before the reader reached page three — and the sender never knew." },
        { "type": "text", "id": "rp2-3", "variant": "body", "content": "Interactive editions inverted the pattern: when a document behaves like a product — tactile pages, media in place, sources one tap away — readers stay, and every interaction is measurable." },
